AGI -&nbsp;No less than six thousand people on the Audace Pier and as many scattered along the banks celebrated today in Trieste the arrival of the school ship Amerigo&nbsp;Vespucci&nbsp; in Trieste. At its entrance into the gulf the oldest unit of the Navy was greeted by the Rombo delle Frecce Tricolori and was escorted by over one thousand three hundred white sails, held on the boats by the crews that every year participate in the Barcolana, today in special edition. A unique show, unpublished by thrills, unforgettable: on the one hand the sea traveled from sustained gusts of bora with the imposing carrier Trieste, the largest unit ever built for the Italian Navy since the Second World War, on the other square Unity of Italy flocked by festive people surrounded by the Fanfara of Carabinieri on horse and the Bersaglieri placed in front of the Royal Staircase.
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
Further there is a maxiscreen with live images of the approaching of the &nbsp;Vespucci, straight bow and lowered sails. To participate in the festival also many children, noisy with the costumes of a carnival now to the sgoccioli. Numerous elders, some with a tricolor flag in hand. But they also saw people with tears in their eyes, moved: mothers, fathers, sister or brother, engaged in sailors of the crew of the school ship who trepidated to reabbreach their loved one. "I haven't seen my daughter for two years. He's boarded. I come from Puglia and I can finally embrace it," said a lady.
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
And here are the celebrations: handshake, rewards and deliveries of "crests" to the commanders of crews by the mayor. So the visits are slowly starting on board. But that's not all. This evening you can not miss a tour in the Village Italy placed between the Molo Bersaglieri and the Molo Audace, with music food &amp; beverage restaurants, shops, sponsor area. In short, the festival continues in honor of the most beautiful in the world until Tuesday.
